interpretation: The "no pedestrians" card represents a blockage or restriction on your path. This could be a physical obstacle or a figurative barrier, such as a rule or law that prevents you from moving forward. It is a reminder to stay aware of your surroundings and to adapt to challenges as they arise. This card can also indicate a need to be cautious and to avoid taking unnecessary risks. Keywords associated with this card include limitation, caution, and boundaries. It is important to assess the situation before proceeding and to find alternate routes or solutions if necessary.
